1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
A single attention head is powerful, but it has a bottleneck.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
It can only learn one type of relationship at a time.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:15,000
To solve this, we split the Query, Key, and Value matrices.

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Now, multiple "heads" can process the same input simultaneously.

5
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:29,000
One head might look for grammatical links, while another looks for sentiment.

6
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Each head computes its own Softmax attention scores independently.

7
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:44,000
After each head calculates its Value update, they must be combined.

8
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:52,000
The results are concatenated side-by-side into a single vector.

9
00:00:52,000 --> 00:01:00,000
A final linear projection mixes these insights back to the original dimension.
